The paper deals with distributed algorithms for consensus in dynamic networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves the study of communication graphs, which is a topic in the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The use of amortized averaging algorithms involves the analysis of the time complexity of the algorithms, which is a topic in the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also involves the use of quantized values, which is a topic in the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the solvability of the 2-set consensus problem, which is a topic in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
